The paper deals with geometric graphs and their properties, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as the most likely category. The paper also discusses algorithms and data structures for recognizing and routing on these graphs, which further supports cs.CG and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as likely categories. The paper also includes results on lower bounds and limits, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses spanners and increasing-chord graphs, which suggests cs.GR (Graph Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as possible categories.
